721420f-a.text:
Madison Ave., west side, south from East 65th to 63rd Streets, showing at the S.W. corner of East 64th Street, a 3-story colonial building occupied by a branch of the Bank of Manhattan Co. This structure erected in 1933 stands upon the site of the former 5-story ,Seth Low home, No. 30 East 64th Street (also bore No. 726 Madison Ave.), The ornate 6-story edifice on the opposite corner (N.W.) is No. 27 East 64th Street (also No. 740-42 Madison Ave.). North of same and appearing on the right is a 3-story gabled building (No. 746) that adjoins the S.W. corner of East 65th Street. Towering over the roof tops of buildings concerned is
the Hotel Pierre.
June 12, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
